on LGBTQ
rights.

04:30.670 --> 04:39.679 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
BARACK OBAMA: I don't think it
is something
that will be reversible, because
American

04:39.713 --> 04:42.115 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
society has changed.

04:42.149 --> 04:46.353 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The attitudes of young people in
particular
have changed.

04:46.386 --> 04:54.628 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
That doesn't mean there aren't
going to be
some fights that are important,
legal issues,

04:54.661 --> 04:58.031 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
issues surrounding transgender
persons.

04:58.064 --> 05:01.101 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
There are still going to be some
battles that
need to take place.

05:01.134 --> 05:06.039 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
JOHN YANG: The president
lamented what he
sees as undue restrictions on
voting rights,

05:06.072 --> 05:09.709 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
