20:05.471 --> 20:10.009 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And because we need it to
achieve good outcomes
as a nation for air and water
quality, we

20:10.042 --> 20:12.745 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
need the partnership of the
states to achieve
that.

20:12.778 --> 20:17.583 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
It is our state regulators who
oftentimes
best understand the local needs
and the uniqueness

20:17.616 --> 20:19.418 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
of our environmental challenges.

20:19.452 --> 20:24.790 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: As Oklahoma
attorney general,
Pruitt filed 14 lawsuits against
the EPA and

20:24.824 --> 20:28.260 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
an array of Obama administration
environmental
rules.

20:28.294 --> 20:32.531 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And, in the past, he's said he
will work to
repeal the president's
centerpiece climate

20:32.565 --> 20:36.368 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
regulation cutting carbon
emissions from power
plants.

20:36.402 --> 20:39.672 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Today, several Democrats raised
concerns over
the health ramifications.

20:39.705 --> 20:41.440 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
SEN.

20:41.474 --> 20:43.576 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
KIRSTEN GILLIBRAND (D), New
York: We have
had children die in New York
City because

20:43.609 --> 20:47.246 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
none of their teachers, no
administrators
in the schools knew what to do
when a child

20:47.279 --> 20:48.747 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
has an asthma attack.

20:48.781 --> 20:50.483 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
It's a huge problem.

20:50.516 --> 20:55.921 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
So, I need you to care about
human health
and really believe that the cost
when human

20:55.955 --> 21:02.228 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
health is at risk, when people
are dying is
far higher than it is the cost
to that polluter

21:02.261 --> 21:04.630 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
to clean up the air and change
their processes.

21:04.663 --> 21:09.502 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
I need you to feel it as if your
children
sitting behind you are the ones
in the emergency

21:09.535 --> 21:10.503 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
room.

21:10.536 --> 21:12.271 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
I need you to know it.

21:12.304 --> 21:13.873 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
SCOTT PRUITT: And, Senator, I
would say to
you there are certain instances
where cost

21:13.906 --> 21:15.641 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
can't even be considered, as you
know.

21:15.674 --> 21:18.744 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Those criteria pollutants under
our NAAQS
program, cost is not even a
factor, because

21:18.777 --> 21:21.313 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
human health is the focus.

21:21.347 --> 21:27.853 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: Environmental
protesters interrupted
the proceedings several times.

21:27.887 --> 21:30.222 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
One was forcibly removed into
the hallway.

21:30.256 --> 21:35.961 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
At various points, some
Democrats showed their
irritation at what they saw as
Pruitt's vague

21:35.995 --> 21:37.730 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
responses.

21:37.763 --> 21:42.067 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
For their part, though,
Republicans praised
Pruitt for his work in Oklahoma,
including

21:42.101 --> 21:47.973 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
his handling of a dispute
involving poultry
industry runoff into the
Illinois River.

21:48.007 --> 21:53.145 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Pruitt negotiated a deal and
ordered further
study, ending the legal fight.

21:53.179 --> 21:58.651 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Democrats pointed to campaign
contributions
Pruitt had received from poultry
company officials.

21:58.684 --> 22:04.290 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But Republicans focused on what
they see as
economic harm and bureaucratic
barriers raised

22:04.323 --> 22:06.158 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
by the EPA.

22:06.192 --> 22:07.893 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Republican Senator Deb Fischer
of Nebraska:

22:07.927 --> 22:09.695 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
SEN.

22:09.728 --> 22:12.164 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
DEB FISCHER (R), Nebraska: As a
result of
the activist role the EPA has
played for the

22:12.198 --> 22:18.103 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
